Implemented US-008 end-to-end with deterministic camera focus transitions and locking behavior.

**What changed**
- Added camera focus interpolation state machine and transition resource in [src/main.rs](/mnt/d/Projects/game/src/main.rs).
- Routed party focus actions (`Take Command`, `Focus Selected Party`) through transition requests instead of snap focus.
- Locked conflicting orbit camera inputs (pan/orbit/zoom/reset) while interpolation is active.
- Added UI transition-state messaging in party panel to clarify locked input + retarget behavior.
- Added deterministic tests for interpolation completion and rapid retarget safety in [src/main.rs](/mnt/d/Projects/game/src/main.rs).
- Logged activity/errors/progress updates in:
  - [.ralph/activity.log](/mnt/d/Projects/game/.ralph/activity.log)
  - [.ralph/errors.log](/mnt/d/Projects/game/.ralph/errors.log)
  - [.ralph/progress.md](/mnt/d/Projects/game/.ralph/progress.md)

